<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-02-27T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-02-27T12:00:00-05:00" n="478" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d478">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Italy/281: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-02-27T12:00:00-05:00">February 27, 1936—noon</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>17. Reference your letter January 31 to the President regarding
                                acquisition of residence as part of settlement of debt which in
                                principle has our unqualified approval.</p>
                            <p>Will you therefore in your discretion take such steps as may be
                                necessary to find out definitely whether a settlement can be
                                arranged and the residence offered as part payment. If a reasonably
                                satisfactory offer is forthcoming along the lines of your letter of
                                January 31, I will be glad to consult our leaders in Congress, since
                                payment in this way necessitates congressional authorization. Please
                                cable developments.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>